Commissioning the studio...
A commission by the studio of Bryan David Snuffer is simply an elegant way of creating a memory! As an investment there is none like it. Bryan would be delighted to speak with you regarding your ideas. In no time you can become the owner of a custom ordered piece of fine art.
Description of the product...
Bryan prefers to work in acrylic paint. Primarily for the exactness and draftsman like quality that can be achieved from the medium. Bryan’s work in acrylic paint has been likened by many seasoned professionals as being so like oils that they could not tell the two apart. With a substrate of tempered hardboard, the acrylic painting becomes very durable and will last for generations to come. Bryan’s greatest skills lay in man and machine.
Commission rates and fees...
The Studio of Bryan David Snuffer has new starting rates and we would like to invite you to call anytime to hear more about basic fees and studio rates. You can also visit our contact forum and let us know what you have in mind. Bryan will contact you right away and we can begin your project! The rates listed below are for artist fees only. Framing and shipping will be invoiced separately at the end of the project.
2017 Commission Rates
Commission rates have been varying and we would like to invite you to call the studio for inquiries.  Mon-Fri 9-5 pm est. (616)607-6038.

*All pricing is negotiable depending on exact client needs.  Please inquire if your project does not fall into one of the categories.  Email me direct at bsnuffer@comcast.net.



*rates are subject to change wthout notice. Special requirements such as travel for research and/or delivery are not included.  In person presention can be arranged with the studio if desired. Costs of transportation, food and lodging are required. These special requirements will be quoted at the time of order.
Terms...
A 1/2 deposit will allow scheduling of your commission on Bryan’s calendar. Upon commencement, Bryan will begin research, referencing, and reviewing of photography. He will produce a detailed graphite sketch for approval. Once the final sketch is approved, Bryan will begin painting the final piece. After finishing the final painting, you have approved the the piece electronically, an additional 1/2 payment is due. Framing can be arranged to your specifications. Framing is included in the price. After framing the painting will be shipped or made ready for in-person presentation. Depending on the schedule of the studio and the length of time before start the down payment may vary. If the studio is more than two months out from starting your project - only 25% down will be be required to schedule a commission.
Getting Started...
Call the studio today at 616-607-6038 and let us know what you are interested in. Our schedule for this year id filling up and we can give you a clear view on the timeline of your project. You can place your 50% down payment with your Visa, Mastercard or Discover card. We also accept checks. Bryan will begin by producing a composite sketch of your image. Depending on size and content your painting can be finished and framed in just several weeks.
Bryan...
is a professional full time artist. He has been painting for the military and collectors for nearly 20 years. His paintings are of a highly realistic nature and attempt to capture the human spirit both past and present.. If you are interested in freezing a moment in your personal experience then Bryan can help you do that. If you are a military unit and wish to commission a piece for a special deployment or occassion please contact Bryan.  His pieces are unique as well as of the highest quality product. Begin the adventure of collecting a piece of fine art that is personalized only for you.



